Article_Name: More Anti-Vaccine Protesters Enter Canada Capital
News Info: Protesters again poured into Canada's capital early Saturday to join a convoy of truckers whose occupation of Ottawa to denounce Covid vaccine mandates is now in its second week.

Article_Name: Missing Tourist Plane Found At Bottom Of Lake In Iceland

Article_Name: "90% vs 10%": Yogi Adityanath's New Math For Poll-Bound UP
News Info: Claiming that the BJP was heading to a landslide victory in Uttar Pradesh assembly polls, Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath on Saturday said that the electoral contest now will be "90 percent versus 10 percent" in favour of his party.

Article_Name: Watch: PM Modi Stops At Research Farm In Hyderabad To Eat 'Chana'
News Info: During his visit to International Crops Research Institute for Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT) in Hyderabad, Prime Minister Narendra Modi walked through the campus on Saturday and tasted some gram (chana) pods directly from the farm.

Article_Name: Lockdown Parties Damaged Public Trust In Government: UK's Rishi Sunak
News Info: UK's Indian-origin Chancellor Rishi Sunak has said that the raging controversy over Downing Street parties has damaged public trust in the government.

Article_Name: Chinese Premier To Imran Khan: Pak A Priority In Neighbourhood Diplomacy
News Info: Chinese Premier Li Keqiang has said Pakistan is a "priority" in China's neighbourhood diplomacy as he met his Pakistani counterpart Imran Khan who ensured him his government will do its utmost to ensure safety of Chinese nationals in his country.

Article_Name: 8-Year-Old Raped For Days By Uncle In Assam: Police
News Info: An eight-year-old girl was allegedly raped by her uncle for several days after he brought her to Guwahati from his parents' place in Kamrup district, a police officer said on Saturday.

Article_Name: YouTuber Remanded To 14-Day Judicial Custody In Maharashtra Students' Protest Case
News Info: Social media influencer Vikas Fhatak alias 'Hindustani bhau' was produced before a magistrate court in Bandra on Saturday after which he was remanded to judicial custody for 14 days.

Article_Name: Sri Lanka's Foreign Minister To Visit India From February 6 To 8
News Info: Sri Lanka's Foreign Minister GL Peiris is scheduled to visit India from Sunday on a three-day visit to strengthen bilateral ties including in areas of trade and connectivity.

Article_Name: KCR Violated Oath Of Office: Congress Leader On His 'New Constitution' Remark
News Info: Congress leader Anand Sharma has slammed Telangana Chief Minister K Chandrashekar Rao over his suggestion that the Constitution should be rewritten and said he has violated his oath of office.

Article_Name: Jo Bole So Nihal, Jai Shri Ram Chants For Yogi Adityanath At UP Gurdwara
News Info: Greeted by both 'Jo Bole so Nihal Sat Sri Akal' and 'Jai Sri Ram', at Mohaddipur Gurudwara in Gorakhpur, Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath on Saturday thanked people for working for his poll campaign like previous elections.

Article_Name: 'World's Largest' Igloo Cafe In J&K's Gulmarg, Can Seat 40 Guests
News Info: An igloo cafe, claimed to be the world's largest, has come up at the famous ski-resort of Gulmarg in Jammu and Kashmir, and has become a centre of attraction for tourists.

Article_Name: Kerala Doctor Gets 6 Years In Jail For Sexually Assaulting Minor Patient
News Info: A 58-year-old doctor was sentenced to six years rigorous imprisonment (RI) on Saturday by a special court in Thiruvananthapuram for sexually assaulting a minor boy in 2017.
